Memory allocation of ArrayList
-> Initially the memory of our ArrayList is 10

new ArrayList<>();  [ _ , _ , _ , _ , _ , _ , _ , _ , _ , _ ]

new memory = old memory + (old memory / 2)
once the memory is full automatically the new memory kicks in


ArrayList vs LinkedList

which is faster to access? ArrayList
while getting an element, which is faster? ArrayList
which has high memory allocation? ArrayList



